descriptionHtml:
[size=5]Hey You,
[/size]
You always wanted to look your Skyrim Fantastic but you don't want to use enb 'cause of the Framerate-drop.
If you answer yes then your right here.When I played Skyrim I always thought to myself:
Man this game looks [color=#ff0000][size=4]bad[/size][/color],even the forested Areas look [color=#ff0000][size=4]bland[/size][/color].
So I used [color=#1e84cc][size=4]Enb[/size][/color],but that had it's problems as well,like The Framedrops on my GTX 760 (3x OC).
Anyways I thought,I want something without Framedrop which looks similary as good but without any framedrop what so ever.
So i tried[size=4] [color=#ff7700]I can't believe it's not[/color][/size] Enb but that didn't look that good.So back to the drawing Board and then I found
[color=#1e84cc][size=5]Imaginator[/size][/color] and created this preset.
Have I bored you to tears yet,yes?Well that's the end,i hope you like the preset.
Just for the record,In the Pictures you can see the entire Preset,you'll get only the screen shots when you download it.

Required: Skse,Skyui,Skyrim newest patch(duh)

[color=#00ff00][size=4]Absolutly recommended Mods[/size][/color](Used in screenshots):

Dynavision:
http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/12525/?

Immersive Saturation Boost:
http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/32064/?

EDWS enhanced Dynamic Weather System:
http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/8739/?

Ultra realistic World Lighting:
http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/13531/?

Realistic Lightning overhaul:
http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/30450/?


[color=#1e84cc][size=4][u][b]Thanks to MyGood Eye for creating Imaginator without it,this preset would never have existed
Thank you all,don't forget to endores if you liked the mod and endores all the mentioned mods[/b][/u][/size][/color]
